('Packaging Instruction Y454   ', 'packaging-instruction-y454', '<p>OPERATOR VARIATIONS: AM-03, DE-01, GA-03, GF-04, IJ-12, KC-11, KQ-08, LH-01, LX-02, LY-04, MH-14, OM-08, OS-03, OU-04, PX-10, SW-02, TN-04, UX-02, VO-03, VT-01, WY-04, XG-01, XK-03, XQ-01</p>\r\n<p>This instruction applies to Films, nitrocellulose base (UN 1324) packed in Limited Quantity.</p>\r\n<p>The General Packing Requirements of Subsection 2.7.5, 5.0.2 to 5.0.4 (with the exception of 5.0.2.3, 5.0.2.5, 5.0.2.11 and 5.0.2.14.2) must be met except that the packagings do not have to meet the marking and testing requirements of 6.0.4 and Subsection 6.3. Packagings must meet the construction criteria specified in Subsection 6.1 and 6.2 and the test criteria specified in Subsection 6.6.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Compatibility Requirements</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Substances must be compatible with their packagings as required by 5.0.2.6.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Closure Requirements</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Closures must meet the requirements of 5.0.2.7.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Limited Quantity Requirements </strong></p>\r\n<p>The requirements of Subsection 2.7 must be met including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>the capability of the package to pass a drop test of 1.2 m;</li>\r\n<li>a 24 hour stacking test;</li>\r\n<li>the gross weight of the completed package must not exceed 30 kg.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Additional Packing Requirements</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Each reel must be place in a tightly closed metal or strong cardboard or fibreboard inner packagings with a cover held in place by adhesive tape or paper;</li>\r\n<li>Fibre drums, plastic drum, plastic jerricans, fibreboard boxes and plastic boxes may only contain 600 m of film or 1 kg of films, whichever is the most restrictive, in one outer packaging.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Single packagings are not permitted.</h4>\r\n<p><img src="https://s5.postimg.cc/5wruxrkav/PI_Y454.jpg" alt="" width="710" height="208" /></p>'),
('Packaging Instruction Y455   ', 'packaging-instruction-y455', '<p>OPERATOR VARIATIONS: AM-03, DE-01, GA-03, GF-04, IJ-12, KQ-08, LH-01, LX-02, LY-04, MH-14, OM-08, OS-03, OU-04, PX-10, SW-02, TN-04, UX-02, VO-03, VT-01, WY-04, XG-01, XK-03, XQ-01</p>\r\n<p>This instruction applies to <strong>Matches, safety</strong> (UN 1944) and <strong>Matches, wax vesta</strong> (UN 1945) packed in Limited Quantities.</p>\r\n<p>The General Packing Requirements of Subsection 2.7.5, 5.0.2 to 5.0.4 (with the exception of 5.0.2.3, 5.0.2.5, 5.0.2.11 and 5.0.2.14.2) must be met except that the packagings do not have to meet the marking and testing requirements of 6.0.4 and Subsection 6.3. Packagings must meet the construction criteria specified in Subsection 6.1 and 6.2 and the test criteria specified in Subsection 6.6.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Compatibility Requirements</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Substances must be compatible with their packagings as required by 5.0.2.6.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Closure Requirements</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Closures must meet the requirements of 5.0.2.7.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Limited Quantity Requirements </strong></p>\r\n<p>The requirements of Subsection 2.7 must be met including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>the capability of the package to pass a drop test of 1.2 m;</li>\r\n<li>a 24 hour stacking test;</li>\r\n<li>the gross weight of the completed package must not exceed 30 kg.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Additional Packing Requirements</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Inner packagings must be securely packed in one of the outer packagings shown below, meeting Packing Group II performance standards;</li>\r\n<li>Matches, safety (book, card or strike on box) must be of the of type that will not ignite spontaneously under normal conditions of air transport and can be readily ignited by friction only by striking on the manufacturer&rsquo;s box, book or card;</li>\r\n<li>Matches must be tightly packed to prevent movement within the package and ignition by rubbing against adjoining more tha